README

last updated: 26-Oct-2010

*installation*
sudo gem1.9.1 install table-formatter
sudo gem1.9.1 install optparse-simple

*recommended installation*
sudo gem1.9.1 install polyrex


Here's a quick start example:

require 'optparse-simple'
require 'polyrex'

polyrex = Polyrex.new('options/option[name,switch,alias,value,mandatory]/error[msg]')

options =<<OPTIONS
username -u --username \\w+ true
  invalid username
  you must enter a username
password -p --pasword \\w+ true
  invalid password
  you must enter a password
keyword   [\\w\+]+ true
  invalid keyword
  you must enter a keyword e.g. --keyword=ruby
OPTIONS

args = %w(-u james -p secret fun)
params = OptParseSimple.new(polyrex.parse(options).to_xml).parse(args)
#=> {:username=>"james", :password=>"secret", :keyword=>"fun"}
